CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 16, 1946, pg. 10, reads: "AUTUMN WEDDING - Miss Catherine L. Darkins, daughter of Mrs. Dorothy Still of Larimer Avenue, and James Jordan, son of Mr. and Mrs. Harry Jordan, were married a few weeks ago in a charming autumn ceremony at the YWCA. The Rev. S. Williams officiated at the ceremony. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of wedding party with six women, including bride Catherine L. Darkins Jordan wearing light colored gown with sheer ruffle around collar; six men, including groom James Jordan; and girl, posed in interior with ferns in background, possibly in YWCA, another version
